name: The Freight Rail Network
description:
Running on almost 140,000 route miles, the U.S. freight rail network is widely considered the world's largest, safest, and most cost-efficient freight system. 
Unlike roadways, U.S. freight railroads are owned by private organizations responsible for their maintenance and improvement projects. 
The lines that you see on the photo it a freight train with almost 60 wagons. Taken at Sierra Grande Rest Area, New Mexico.
